File: Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - The Judicial Conduct Committee has ordered Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng to publicly apologise for his pro-Israel comments.
In a webinar hosted by The Jerusalem Post last year, Mogoeng expressed his love and support for Israel. He cited Biblical references to justify his comments. READ: Chief Justice Mogoeng prays against 'vaccines of the devil' Africa 4 Palestine, a pro-Palestine organisation, laid a complaint about Mogoeng's comments. They argued Mogoeng's remarks contravened the judicial ethical rules. He's also been ordered to retract his utterances. READ: ANC concerned about Mogoeng comments The committee has even told the Chief Justice what to say in his apology and retraction. Mogoeng has to apologise within 10 days.